 cask holding 84&nbsp;<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wine_gallon"=
 title=3D"Wine gallon">wine gallons</a> and a wine <a href=3D"https://en.wi=
kipedia.org/wiki/Tierce_(unit)" title=3D"Tierce (unit)">tierce</a> as holdi=
ng 42&nbsp;wine gallons. Custom had made the 42&nbsp;gallon watertight tier=
ce a standard container for shipping eel, salmon, herring, molasses, wine, =
whale oil, and many other commodities in the English colonies by 1700. Afte=
r the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/American_Revolution" title=
=3D"American Revolution">American Revolution</a> in 1776, American merchant=
s continued to use the same size barrels.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-oilbblhist_9-0=
" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Barrel_(unit=
)#cite_note-oilbblhist-9"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>9<span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
